The Nairobi Expressway was adopted as a remedy for the traffic congestion in and out of the capital’s central business district.KeNHA will partner with Kenya Forest Service in not only beautification of the road but also reinstatement of vegetation cover. The Kenyan economy loses about Sh11 million per hour, or more than Sh100 billion annually, to traffic congestion. The traffic situation in Nairobi alone costs the economy over Sh50 million per day in lost productivity. 

Nairobi is the fourth-most congested city globally. 

The Nairobi Expressway was adopted as a remedy for the traffic congestion in and out of the capital’s central business district. Expected to revolutionise traffic in the Nairobi Metropolitan Area, it is the solution to decongesting the city through provision of a faster and reliable road transport network. The four-lane dual carriageway with 11 interchanges is a convenient and alternative route for motorists. 



