Relocation of utilities has also begun. Kenya Power has relocated 106 kilometres of power lines between Mlolongo and James Gichuru Road while relocation of water pipes is already complete. 

The JKIA-Westlands expressway will offer value for travel time savings, the benefits businesses and organisations get from reduced travel times. Nairobi Metropolitan Area Transport Authority (NaMATA) reports show, for instance, the average travel time between Mlolongo and Westlands is two hours instead of just 15 minutes. 

Shorter travel time also means a reduction of exhaust emissions. That not only allows for cleaner air but also clearer sky, protecting the Ozone layer. 

Traffic noise 

Fuel consumption is a key concern. Its reduction will enable motorists to expend the saved amounts in other areas of the economy. The level of traffic noise will also reduce significantly, offering motorists a much-relaxed driving and travel experience. 

The measures taken to reinstate the environment or even improve on what existed is what makes an infrastructure project stand out. Several have been outlined to ensure minimal interruptions to the environment or reinstatement after completion. 



